{"id":21370,"date":"2015-12-21T14:26:14","date_gmt":"2015-12-21T10:26:14","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=21370"},"modified":"2023-12-18T10:03:53","modified_gmt":"2023-12-18T06:03:53","slug":"dua-cant-memorize-quran","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2015\/12\/21\/dua-cant-memorize-quran\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Dua: If you cannot memorize Quran, recite supplications"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abdullah ibn Abi Awfa reported: A man came to the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and he said, \u201cI cannot memorize anything from the Quran, so teach me what will suffice me.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Say: Glory be to Allah, all praise is due to Allah, there is no God but Allah, Allah is the greatest, and there is no movement or might but in Allah the Exalted, the Almighty.<\/strong>\u201d The man said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, these words are for Allah, but what is for me?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Say: O Allah, have mercy on me, provide for me, forgive me, and guide me.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 832<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0623\u064e\u0648\u0652\u0641\u064e\u0649 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u00a0 \u062c\u064e\u0627\u0621\u064e \u0631\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u064c \u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0646\u0651\u0650\u064a \u0644\u064e\u062